    <item>
      <title>Unbounded-Time Safety Verification of Stochastic Differential Dynamics</title>
      <link>https://fiction-zju.github.io/pulp/20-06-04-pulp-sdes/</link>
      <pubDate>Thu, 04 Jun 2020 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>https://fiction-zju.github.io/pulp/20-06-04-pulp-sdes/</guid>
      <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;While writing my book [Stochastic Processes] I had an argument with Feller. He asserted that everyone said &amp;lsquo;random variable&amp;rsquo; and I asserted that everyone said &amp;lsquo;chance variable&amp;rsquo;. We obviously had to use the same name in our books, so we decided the issue by a stochastic procedure. That is, we tossed for it and he won.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ndash; &lt;cite&gt;Joseph L. Doob, 1910 &amp;ndash; 2004&lt;/cite&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A &lt;a href=&#34;https://mp.weixin.qq.com/s/pdGlYIHiywD7sdkEDsG9AQ&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;blog post&lt;/a&gt; (in Chinese) for &lt;a href=&#34;https://fiction-zju.github.io/publication/feng-cav2020/&#34;&gt;this publication&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    
